-- Schalke May Sign Chelsea’s Benitez as Manager, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-05-05T12:43:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-05/schalke-may-sign-chelsea-s-benitez-as-manager-sunday-times-says.html
 Germany’s Schalke may try to sign
Chelsea’s interim soccer manager  Rafael Benitez , the Sunday
Times reported.  Benitez, who has guided the Blues to the Europa League
final, is due to leave the team at the end of the season. Ruhr-
based Schalke is looking for a “big name” manager to challenge
Bayern Munich and  Borussia Dortmund , the Times added.  Bayern has already clinched this year’s Bundesliga title
and will meet second-placed Dortmund in Europe’s Champions
League final on May 25. Schalke is fourth, behind Bayer
Leverkusen.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  